==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scapple
<hw>Scap"ple</hw> <pr>(sk⟦acr⟧p"p'l)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
OF. <ets>eskapeler</ets>, <ets>eschapler</ets>, to cut, hew, LL.
<ets>scapellare</ets>. Cf. <er>Scabble</er>.]</ety> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>To
work roughly, or shape without finishing, as stone before leaving the
quarry.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>To dress in any way short of fine
tooling or rubbing, as stone.</def> <rj><au>Gwilt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scapula</ent>⟦br⟧
